post_text:
Cool Tools info!!!

Cool Tools will be today, Tuesday August 18, 9-11am and 5-7:30pm. This is available to any registered student in Felicity Franklin school district.

Cool Tools will be held in the new high school gym, where you vote. There will be signs to enter and exit, the school will not be open to the public. Please maintain social distancing.

We are providing supplies for K - high school.
We have plenty of supplies, this is not a first come first served!

Masks are required to enter the building and we are only allowing 10 in at a time (in addition to the volunteers) so please only one member per family if possible.

We will be providing lanyards and water bottles to each student and a sign up sheet for masks. Those are incredibly expensive so we don't want to give them away if your student doesn't need them. They will be made available through the school.

post_text: Garet is showing his school spirit and smile . He says he likes that the teachers make learning fun. It isn't just sit in you seat all day and be bored. He likes that he has opportunities outside of the classroom like student council, the play (that will hopefully be rescheduled), after school homework time, and the trip with Byways to Pittsburgh. My dad has lived in Felicity for 47 years, most of them spent at the school. He loves it and I love it. It is a family tradition.

Good evening Felicity-Franklin Families,

We wanted to first communicate our deepest sympathies and sincere thoughts for the men, women and families of the Clermont County Sheriff‚Äôs Department.

We also wanted you to know that we are planning to discuss our support plan tomorrow morning and encourage the involvement of staff and students in the coming days. This will allow us to speak to all students and staff, ensuring that we have consistent and respectful communication throughout our school family.

There will be some tough days ahead, together we can help each other and honor those who serve us at such great personal cost.

post_text:
The Great Kindness Challenge 2019

Felicity-Franklin Middle School is participating in The Great Kindness Challenge this year. It is one school week (January 29-February 1) devoted to performing as many acts of kindness as possible. Developing the habit of kindness has the power to increase tolerance, unity and respect for all. This is the first year that our school has proudly participated in this proactive, positive, nation-wide bully prevention program.

You will see one of the checklists below come home with your child January 28th. We have many fun activities planned for the week. Thank you for supporting this initiative in our community.

We welcome any and all participation from parents, caregivers, and community members.
